Class
Description
DataArray
Class for holding a list of values of a specific type.
DoubleList
A List implementation wrapper for a native double array.
FloatList
A List implementation wrapping a native float array.
Formatter
A class capable of formatting (i.e write as text) numbers so that they get uniform appearance and can be presented together, typically in a column with decimal symbol aligned etc.
GpxReader
Reader for reading GPX files into TimeSeries.JSON.
Indentation
Class for holding a space indentation commonly used at beginning of pretty printed lines.
IntList
A List implementation wrapping a native int array.
ISO8601DateParser
Date parser for the ISO 8601 format.
JsonUtil
A collection of utilities for the Log I/O JSON module.
RunningPercentile
Class for computing the running percentile (such as median) for a set of observations without holding any of the observations.
Signal
Model a time series signal as it is defined by the TimeSeries.JSON format.
Statistics
Class for computing running statistics on a data stream.
TimeSeries
Class representing the content of one TimeSeries.JSON entry.
TimeSeriesDataListener
Provides a mechanism for the client to monitor and process data during a time series read operation, and also to abort the process in case that is requested by user or for other reasons.
TimeSeriesReader
Class for reading TimeSeries.JSON files.
TimeSeriesUtil
Utility methods for working with time series.
TimeSeriesWriter
Class for writing TimeSeries.JSON entries to disk.
Util
A collection of useful utilities for time series.
WellKnownProperty
List the well known properties of the TimeSeries.JSON format.
XmlUtil
Convenience methods that makes up for the terrible API of the standard JDK XML package.
